        "title": "using constructor wit new object in Java",
        "body": "<pre><code>public class swap\n{\n    public class Point\n    {\n        public int x=0;\n        public int y=0;\n\n        public Point(int a, int b)\n        {\n            this.x = a;\n            this.y = b;\n        }\n\n        public void swapxy(Point p)\n        {\n            int t;\n\n            t = p.x;\n            p.x = p.y;\n            p.y = t;\n        }\n\n        public String ToString()\n        {\n            return (\"x=\"+x+\" y=\"+y);\n        }\n    }\n\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) \n    {\n        Point pxy = Point(10,20);\n\n        pxy.swapxy(pxy);\n        System.out.println(pxy);\n\n    }\n\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I am getting method is undefined error for <code>Point pxy = Point(10,20);<\/code> what is wrong ?<\/p>\n",
