            "creation_date": 1456317945,
            "body": "<p>You've forgotten the <code>new<\/code> keyword:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Point pxy = new Point(10,20);\n            ↑↑↑\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 35602617,
            "question_id": 35602567
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-6fH5pGQO0rs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAaQ/eckzOFHZXOo/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 5704855,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4508754,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4508754/paulo-santos",
                "reputation": 42,
                "display_name": "Paulo Santos"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 3,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1456514681,
            "creation_date": 1456318045,
            "body": "<p>You forget to write the New after the \"=\";<\/p>\n\n<p>The correct way is like that:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Point pxy = new Point(10,20);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Oh, the point is that the class you want to use is an innerClass of Swap, so you must instantiate it before you use it.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you dont need this to be in an inner class, declare this class in a separated file, or you can do as the code bellow:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> public class Swap {\n        //add static in the class to access it in a static way\n         public static class Point\n        {\n//change the attributes to private, this is a good practice\n            private int x=0;\n            private int y=0;\n\n            public Point(int a, int b)\n            {\n                this.x = a;\n                this.y = b;\n            }\n\n            public void swapxy(Point p)\n            {\n                int t;\n\n                t = p.x;\n                p.x = p.y;\n                p.y = t;\n            }\n\n            public String ToString()\n            {\n                return (\"x=\"+x+\" y=\"+y);\n            }\n        }\n\n         public static void main(String[] args){\n\n              Swap.Point pxy = new Swap.Point(10,20); \n              System.out.println(pxy.ToString());\n         }\n\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 35602654,
            "question_id": 35602567,
            "last_edit_date": 1456514681
        },
        {
